"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-boxing-samoan-boxer-highlights-mental-struggle-coach-death-paris-olympics-village\", \"text\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article.  BIGGER THAN SPORTS. Belgian boxer Victor Schelstraete (blue) and Samoan Ato Plodzicki-Faoagali (red) pictured during the round of 16 preliminaries of the men's 92kg category at the Olympic Games in Paris, France, July 28, 2024.  Dirk Waem/Belga via Reuters  PARIS, France - After fighting his way to the Paris Games and giving himself a shot at an Olympic medal, Samoa's Ato Plodzicki-Faoagali said the death of his coach had left him struggling mentally.  CoachLionel Elika Fatupaito diedon Friday, July 26, while at the Olympic Village, ahead of Plodzicki-Faoagali's heavyweight bout against Victor Schelstraete of Belgium.  While the 25-year-old did receive some help from Papua New Guinea's boxing coach Peter Morrison, he was beaten handily by Schelstraete, who left the Samoan bleeding from the cheek.  \\\"I was thinking about pulling out \\u2026 it's been hard,\\\" Pacific Games champion Plodzicki-Faoagali said.  \\\"It's been hard to stay strong. I have been struggling mentally the past few days. I thought I was going to win a medal for sure, but it's been really hard mentally. I do not care about the medal right now.  \\\"Even through these hard times, I appreciate everyone. I am going to come back stronger and chase my dreams.\\\"  Schelstraete, who spoke to Plodzicki-Faoagali before and after the fight and held up his opponent's arm in the ring, said the Samoan had displayed great spirit just by showing up.  \\\"Big respect to him. He's got a big heart. He honored his coach by fighting,\\\" Schelstraete said.  \\\"These coaches, they are very selfless. They put in all their work for us to get here, and for him to not be here to experience that moment, it's very sad.\\\"  Asked if it was hard to fight in the bout, Schelstraete said: \\\"I had to put that aside. Because I felt genuinely sorry for him. But you have to put the emotions aside.\\\"  Schelstraete meets Spain's Enmanuel Reyes on Thursday.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"